scripts.text: A massive stone head lies here, cracked and half sideways in the wet earth. Its empty eye sockets stare blindly skywards.

In a secluded glade you find a small shrine made of moss-covered stone.

From the carvings you judge it to be a shrine to The Weaver, Thyra, the remote Mistress of Fate who spins the threads of destiny, weaving together the tales of all beings.

events.flavourText:
Suddenly, a group of fierce looking reptiles rush out of the undergrowth and confront you!

They regard you with eyes that glint with malicious intelligence. The situation is tense...

scripts.text:
This clearing is heavily overgrown with ferms, all rustling in the gentle breeze. 

You regard is suspiciously, but as far as you can tell the glade is empty...

events.flavourText: The dirt path runs through a peaceful looking glade and wends it's way around some strange looking clumps of bush.

You pause and cast a suspicious eye over the bushes. 

For a moment nothing moves in the glade.
Suddenly, with little more than an eery rustle, the real danger here emerges from the trees around you!

... the smell of humidity and fresh vegetation assaults your nostrils and your eyes are dazzled by sudden brightness. You freeze momentarily as your senses recover.

You are standing in a lush tropical forest. Broad leaved trees sway overhead and the foliage under foot is springy and moist. In the distance you hear a strange bird's shriek that is answered by a chorus of other foreign sounds. The air is thick and clammy.

What you can see of the horizon is dominated by jagged cliffs on all sides; perhaps you are in some kind of basin?

Of more interest to you is a dirt path nearby. It appears that you may be approaching inhabited areas.

scripts.text:
All of a sudden your skin crawls. You are certain that you are being watched!

You freeze and stand ready to defend yourself.
Nothing happens. Perhaps you were mistaken.
This section of path appears to be losing the battle with the encroaching jungle.

events.flavourText: A shadow suddenly passes rapidly over the forest around you, and a distant shriek echoes from above.
You glance at the sky and catch a fleeting glimpse of something large disappearing northwards.
But you have no time to track it's course for, as if answering the creature's shrieking call, a flock of small reptiles decend out of the trees to attack you!

scripts.text: The air within the cave is chill and damp. Smells of minerals and mildew assail you, strangely at odds with the thick tropical jungle outside. Everything is eerily silent.

events.flavourText: You enter a dark cavern, every surface slick with condensation. Scattered fungi emit a faint bioluminescent glow.

Other luminescent forms detach from the ceiling and drift dreamily down towards you. You marvel at the pretty lights.

It takes a moment to realise that you are under attack!

scripts.text:
In the corner of this small cave lies a still pool of phosphorescent water. Tiny glowing motes drift slowly upwards from the dark water surface.

It looks very deep.
Something about the chamber makes you feel peaceful and safe. You're not sure why.

events.flavourText: The way is blocked by a gigantic snail, glowing faintly in the low light.

At first you think the beast is asleep, but slowly it opens a single lid and regards you with one cold eye.

It doesn't look friendly.
You back away. The snail slowly closes it's eye.
The water in the pool is cold and clear. It shimmers fainlty in your cupped hand.
You pick a handful of berries off the bush.
You pick a handful of berries off the bush.
Examining the face more closely, you note that the eye sockets form narrow tunnels into the depths of the stone head. It's pitch black in there.

mazeScripts.flavourText: You reach an arm as deep as you can into the empty socket and feel around.

At first you can't feel anything, not even the bottom. 

Then your fingers brush something hard and warm!
With an angry chitter and hiss, a swarm of large roaches explode out of the dark recess!

events.flavourText: Rummaging through the remains of several previous victims, you find a number of useful things that they will no longer need.
